{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Preheat oven to 275°F. Line two baking sheets with parchment and set aside."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"isHeader":false,"content":" <b>Insert butterfly whisk<b>. Add egg whites and salt and without measuring cup whisk <b>10 min\/100°F\/speed 2<b> until thick and glossy. <b>Remove butterfly whisk.<b> "},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Gently transfer mixture into a large icing bag with the end cut (approx. ½ in. when lying flat). Pipe meringue into ghost shapes directly onto prepared baking sheets, starting with a circle (approx. 1½ in. diameter) and spiraling upward to a point for the top of the ghost's head. Leave a 2 inch space between ghosts to allow for spreading. Carefully press two chocolate chip eyes into each meringue ghost."},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Bake for 40 minutes (275°F). Turn oven off immediately after 40 minutes and allow meringues to completely cool down inside closed oven (approx. 3 hr. or overnight). Slide spatula under meringues to release and serve."}],"usefulItems":"parchment paper, icing bag, baking sheets (approx. 16 in. x 14 in.), oven","id":"r164510","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-h0gNdSiWtak\/XZWexCTHDKI\/AAAAAAAAe5c\/ppvKHrzjn3IlJdL4MRxsqH2xb80xrDQHgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_gxWFTiP6z830dPJJ.png","title":"Meringue Ghosts","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"9 ½ oz sugar"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"3 ½ oz egg whites, from large eggs (approx. 3-4 eggs), room temperature"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"&frac18; tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"mini chocolate chips, to make ghost eyes"}],"nutrition":["per 1 piece","305 kJ \/ 73 kcal","1 g","17 g","0 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["For best results, make sure mixing bowl, mixing bowl lid and butterfly whisk are thoroughly clean and dry before starting meringues. Any residual grease or moisture will prevent eggs from properly aerating. Eggs at room temperature provide best results.","Store Meringue Ghosts in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week.","Can also be garnished with sprinkles.","Once cooled, dip bottoms of meringue ghosts in melted chocolate, gently scrape off excess chocolate and allow to set. Do not refrigerate as they will absorb moisture from the refrigerator and lose their crispness."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","12h 25m","16 pieces"]}